1
00:00:05,904 --> 00:00:07,237
[Episode 11]
The place next to Gil Da Ran

2
00:00:07,237 --> 00:00:08,570
is for Seo Yun Jae.

3
00:00:10,637 --> 00:00:12,937
When he comes back,

4
00:00:12,937 --> 00:00:15,870
Kang Gyeong Jun will disappear.

5
00:00:15,870 --> 00:00:18,137
I will disappear for good.

6
00:00:18,537 --> 00:00:21,537
I'll be living it up somewhere

7
00:00:21,537 --> 00:00:24,904
so you just worry about Seo Yun Jae.

8
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:32,404
You're just going to disappear?

9
00:00:32,404 --> 00:00:35,603
Are you going to come after me?

10
00:00:37,137 --> 00:00:39,537
If you don't get your act together,

11
00:00:39,537 --> 00:00:41,704
I may whisk you off.

12
00:00:49,503 --> 00:00:51,304
Your shoelace is untied.

13
00:00:51,704 --> 00:00:54,037
I told you to get your act together.

14
00:00:54,037 --> 00:00:58,071
I'm going to soar, so don't look back

15
00:00:58,071 --> 00:01:00,470
and you can be on your way.

16
00:01:01,338 --> 00:01:04,438
Let's make it work until then.

17
00:01:07,404 --> 00:01:09,271
Okay.

18
00:01:10,770 --> 00:01:13,237
You look like you're in so much pain.

19
00:01:13,237 --> 00:01:15,537
I'm just a kid. I shouldn't have to worry
about an adult like you.

20
00:01:15,537 --> 00:01:16,904
It's burdensome.

21
00:01:16,904 --> 00:01:18,071
I know.

22
00:01:18,071 --> 00:01:21,204
I shouldn't be like this.

23
00:01:21,204 --> 00:01:25,071
I need to get my act together.

24
00:01:27,503 --> 00:01:29,904
Is the shoelace tied tight?

25
00:01:29,904 --> 00:01:31,637
It's tied super tight.

26
00:01:31,637 --> 00:01:32,970
Is it okay?

27
00:01:32,970 --> 00:01:34,603
It definitely won't come loose.

28
00:01:34,603 --> 00:01:36,004
Let's go.

29
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:39,704
Are you sure it's not cutting off
your blood circulation?

30
00:01:40,304 --> 00:01:41,438
I'm fine.

31
00:01:41,438 --> 00:01:42,970
Let's go.

32
00:01:48,837 --> 00:01:50,870
Come on.

33
00:01:57,670 --> 00:02:00,371
Eating like that can mess up your system.

34
00:02:01,237 --> 00:02:02,904
You're messing up my system
by staring at me.

35
00:02:02,904 --> 00:02:04,537
You should go to bed.

36
00:02:04,537 --> 00:02:07,104
How am I such a bother?

37
00:02:07,104 --> 00:02:08,704
Because I'm young?

38
00:02:09,904 --> 00:02:14,204
A smart and handsome kid with a lot
of money can do well anywhere.

39
00:02:14,204 --> 00:02:16,104
I'd never mooch off you, not even
for a single bite of your noodles,

40
00:02:16,104 --> 00:02:18,804
so don't you worry.

41
00:02:18,804 --> 00:02:20,603
But you'll be all alone once
you return to your body.

42
00:02:20,603 --> 00:02:23,137
If that's what's bothering you, don't worry.

43
00:02:25,570 --> 00:02:27,937
I'm going to find my father.

44
00:02:39,237 --> 00:02:40,704
Mary,

45
00:02:40,704 --> 00:02:42,904
this doesn't seem like your first time.

46
00:02:42,904 --> 00:02:46,770
I've built up my expertise
from stalking Gyeong Jun.

47
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:52,470
Wow. These are amazing.

48
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:55,438
The pictures are so vivid and animated.

49
00:02:58,570 --> 00:02:59,804
Who's that?

50
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:03,470
Please tell me anything you can
about the man you met in New York,

51
00:03:03,470 --> 00:03:07,338
the man Hui Su was going to marry.

52
00:03:07,970 --> 00:03:11,137
I have no leads on Gyeong Jun's whereabouts.

53
00:03:11,137 --> 00:03:16,371
I did hear he had a daughter
around Gyeong Jun's age.

54
00:03:16,371 --> 00:03:19,237
Her name was Mary.

55
00:03:20,404 --> 00:03:21,970
Mary.

56
00:03:22,338 --> 00:03:24,637
Get out of the way.

57
00:03:35,404 --> 00:03:38,970
Yun Jae and Da Ran are meeting us
at the hotel lobby.

58
00:03:38,970 --> 00:03:42,338
Don't bring up anything that will
cause us to raise our voices.

59
00:03:42,338 --> 00:03:44,537
Gyeong Jun may be in Korea.

60
00:03:45,171 --> 00:03:47,171
I think I might be able to find him.

61
00:03:47,171 --> 00:03:49,404
This is the first time I'll be
seeing Yun Jae's father.

62
00:03:49,404 --> 00:03:51,570
Yun Jae's mother doesn't like seeing him,

63
00:03:51,570 --> 00:03:53,304
so I didn't have to see him, either.

64
00:03:54,037 --> 00:03:57,870
I met him when our families
met to discuss our wedding.

65
00:03:57,870 --> 00:04:00,304
He's very quiet and rather unapproachable.

66
00:04:00,304 --> 00:04:01,970
He's a doctor too.

67
00:04:03,237 --> 00:04:05,438
Is that why you've come?

68
00:04:06,271 --> 00:04:08,603
I'm not getting myself involved,

69
00:04:09,037 --> 00:04:12,637
so don't tell Yun Jae either.

70
00:04:13,737 --> 00:04:16,870
He's Yun Jae's brother and your son.

71
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:19,071
Don't you feel sorry for him? He's all alone.

72
00:04:22,937 --> 00:04:24,970
He's not my son.

73
00:04:25,371 --> 00:04:28,338
He's Kang Hui Su's son.

74
00:04:28,804 --> 00:04:31,804
I'm perfectly happy with having had
just my mom in my life,

75
00:04:31,804 --> 00:04:35,104
but he is someone my mom loved,

76
00:04:35,104 --> 00:04:37,570
so I am curious about him.

77
00:04:38,271 --> 00:04:44,004
It was you who had asked Hui Su
to have a baby for us.

78
00:04:46,537 --> 00:04:48,937
I didn't need a baby.

79
00:04:48,937 --> 00:04:51,570
I needed the umbilical cord

80
00:04:51,570 --> 00:04:54,503
because it was the only way
we could save Yun Jae.

81
00:04:54,503 --> 00:04:57,037
You had agreed to it too.

82
00:04:57,537 --> 00:05:02,071
Do you think you'll be able to face him
as your son after all this time?

83
00:05:02,071 --> 00:05:05,804
He came into being not out of love
but out of necessity.

84
00:05:06,204 --> 00:05:11,338
You just dumped that kid on Hui Su too.

85
00:05:11,904 --> 00:05:14,537
I think my father does want to meet me

86
00:05:14,537 --> 00:05:16,338
if he's left behind something like this.

87
00:05:16,704 --> 00:05:20,171
In any case, I'm sure I came into being
because he loved my mother very much.

88
00:05:20,704 --> 00:05:22,670
I wonder why there are two babies.

89
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:25,104
Do you think you might have a brother?

90
00:05:25,104 --> 00:05:27,304
A brother?

91
00:05:27,304 --> 00:05:29,670
I suppose that's not out of the question.

92
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:35,371
Promise me you won't tell Yun Jae

93
00:05:35,371 --> 00:05:37,404
about the child.

94
00:05:38,737 --> 00:05:44,104
I won't remind him of anything
he can't remember.

95
00:06:07,037 --> 00:06:09,271
Hi.

96
00:06:11,271 --> 00:06:13,603
Hello, mom.

97
00:06:18,304 --> 00:06:20,204
It's been a long time.

98
00:06:20,204 --> 00:06:23,603
Yes, dad.

99
00:06:35,837 --> 00:06:38,704
I'm sorry I couldn't
make it to the wedding.

100
00:06:38,704 --> 00:06:39,804
It's okay.

101
00:06:39,804 --> 00:06:41,237
Wait.

102
00:06:41,737 --> 00:06:43,904
We should go up to the room.

103
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:47,404
Your father brought you a wedding gift.

104
00:06:47,404 --> 00:06:48,770
It won't take long.

105
00:06:48,770 --> 00:06:49,837
Let's go.

106
00:06:54,404 --> 00:06:56,071
I'll be right back.

107
00:07:01,904 --> 00:07:05,204
I heard you've been ill. I'm sorry
I haven't been able to come by.

108
00:07:05,204 --> 00:07:06,937
Are you better now?

109
00:07:07,637 --> 00:07:09,304
No.

110
00:07:09,304 --> 00:07:13,171
I know you're my father, but you
seem like a stranger to me.

111
00:07:13,171 --> 00:07:15,271
You'll get better with time.

112
00:07:15,704 --> 00:07:18,970
We're father and son.
We're definitely not strangers.

113
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:22,970
I'm your only son, so I must
mean a lot to you and mom.

114
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:26,204
Our only son?

115
00:07:27,603 --> 00:07:31,237
You really don't remember.

116
00:07:31,237 --> 00:07:32,603
What do you mean?

117
00:07:32,603 --> 00:07:34,271
It's nothing.

118
00:07:34,804 --> 00:07:38,037
- Are you still on leave?
- Yes.

119
00:07:39,304 --> 00:07:41,071
Oh, wow.

120
00:07:41,537 --> 00:07:43,338
Do you know him?

121
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:44,904
Don't you remember Professor Park Min Gyu?

122
00:07:44,904 --> 00:07:47,304
So he knows Seo Yun Jae?

123
00:07:47,304 --> 00:07:49,104
Yes.

124
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:52,204
It's as your mom said.

125
00:07:52,204 --> 00:07:55,404
You're like a different person.

126
00:07:55,404 --> 00:07:57,704
I'll come back to my old self soon.

127
00:07:57,704 --> 00:07:59,438
Of course.

128
00:08:19,404 --> 00:08:21,770
I may seem unfamiliar to you,

129
00:08:21,770 --> 00:08:25,204
but just consider me a different son
who's come for a short visit.

130
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:35,737
A group of doctors' wives

131
00:08:35,737 --> 00:08:38,570
are getting together this weekend.

132
00:08:38,570 --> 00:08:40,704
You should come with me.

133
00:08:41,237 --> 00:08:42,603
Pardon?

134
00:08:42,603 --> 00:08:46,704
It's a volunteer group I've been
a part of since I got married.

135
00:08:46,704 --> 00:08:50,004
I'd like to introduce you
to everyone while I'm in Korea.

136
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:52,004
Okay.

137
00:08:52,004 --> 00:08:56,470
Do you always dress like that?

138
00:08:58,870 --> 00:08:59,904
Yes.

139
00:08:59,904 --> 00:09:03,970
We should go shopping before the gathering.

140
00:09:03,970 --> 00:09:07,503
You don't have your own car, right?

141
00:09:07,503 --> 00:09:11,004
We should get you a car, too.

142
00:09:11,404 --> 00:09:14,171
But I don't need a car.

143
00:09:14,171 --> 00:09:17,371
You need one if you don't
want Yun Jae to lose face.

144
00:09:17,371 --> 00:09:18,937
If you had tended to such things yourself,

145
00:09:18,937 --> 00:09:22,004
I wouldn't have to worry about these things.

146
00:09:23,037 --> 00:09:25,338
I'm sorry.

147
00:09:28,371 --> 00:09:30,537
She's doing it so that I don't lose face,

148
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:33,438
so you shouldn't say, "I'm sorry."

149
00:09:33,438 --> 00:09:38,204
Look her in the eye and say, "Thank you."

150
00:09:38,204 --> 00:09:40,737
Da Ran's rather timid,

151
00:09:40,737 --> 00:09:43,338
but I'm shameless, so let me
thank you instead.

152
00:09:44,171 --> 00:09:46,537
Give me your credit card.

153
00:09:48,371 --> 00:09:50,904
You don't have to make time
out of your busy schedule.

154
00:09:50,904 --> 00:09:54,271
I'll get her what she needs
for the sake of saving my face.

155
00:09:54,271 --> 00:09:56,970
How much do you think it'll take
to save face, for my sake.

156
00:09:58,137 --> 00:10:01,737
I need to know the exact value you've set
for the sake of saving my face.

157
00:10:01,737 --> 00:10:03,537
Yun Jae,

158
00:10:03,537 --> 00:10:06,438
is it so wrong of me to want
to do volunteer work with her?

159
00:10:06,438 --> 00:10:09,970
If you have to get a new car and clothes,
it's not volunteer work.

160
00:10:09,970 --> 00:10:11,470
It's a money-flaunting gathering.

161
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:12,537
Yun Jae.

162
00:10:12,537 --> 00:10:13,837
Sir...

163
00:10:13,837 --> 00:10:16,304
I mean, dad, you should
spend more time with her

164
00:10:16,304 --> 00:10:19,037
if you don't want her involved
in strange organizations.

165
00:10:19,438 --> 00:10:21,670
It's not a strange organization.

166
00:10:21,670 --> 00:10:25,770
It's an exclusive club for the wives
of famous directors of hospitals.

167
00:10:25,770 --> 00:10:30,204
But then you and Da Ran

168
00:10:30,204 --> 00:10:32,970
are not qualified to be in that club.

169
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:34,937
Dad's not a director.

170
00:10:36,404 --> 00:10:37,804
Yun Jae,

171
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:43,271
your father was an acclaimed doctor.

172
00:10:43,271 --> 00:10:45,271
Right?

173
00:10:47,237 --> 00:10:49,737
That's not good enough.

174
00:10:49,737 --> 00:10:52,304
You need to step it up and set up
your own practice.

175
00:10:52,304 --> 00:10:55,037
I'd be too ashamed to have her
meet anyone until you do.

176
00:10:55,537 --> 00:10:59,937
She'd lose face at
the money-flaunting gathering.

177
00:10:59,937 --> 00:11:01,470
Yun Jae,

178
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:07,037
your father was the director
of a hospital before going to Africa.

179
00:11:07,037 --> 00:11:08,737
Right?

180
00:11:10,704 --> 00:11:12,670
Yes.

181
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:16,171
You may not remember, but I was
a director of a hospital.

182
00:11:16,171 --> 00:11:18,304
But not anymore.

183
00:11:18,304 --> 00:11:20,837
Stop arguing with me, and just
give me your credit card.

184
00:11:24,204 --> 00:11:25,637
Are you really going to buy a car?

185
00:11:25,637 --> 00:11:28,503
They're very thorough. They don't say
what they don't mean.

186
00:11:28,503 --> 00:11:30,237
You were there. They couldn't stop

187
00:11:30,237 --> 00:11:32,704
showing off about how he used to be
a director of a hospital.

188
00:11:33,304 --> 00:11:35,837
It would be rude of us not to
take up on their offer.

189
00:11:35,837 --> 00:11:39,104
I don't think she was serious
about getting me a car.

190
00:11:39,104 --> 00:11:40,704
This will be good for you.

191
00:11:40,704 --> 00:11:41,670
Why don't you test drive it?

192
00:11:41,670 --> 00:11:44,670
I don't need a car. I'm not
a good driver anyway.

193
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:46,137
Fine then.

194
00:11:46,137 --> 00:11:47,904
I'll get a nice one for myself.

195
00:11:50,371 --> 00:11:51,904
This one.

196
00:11:52,603 --> 00:11:54,371
Gyeong Jun.

197
00:11:55,438 --> 00:11:57,438
From here

198
00:11:59,704 --> 00:12:01,570
to here.

199
00:12:03,137 --> 00:12:06,104
How can I get them without
even trying them on?

200
00:12:06,104 --> 00:12:07,770
Then try them on.

201
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:12,004
But I don't need this.

202
00:12:12,004 --> 00:12:14,470
Not bad. Get it.

203
00:12:16,037 --> 00:12:19,271
I'm really fine.

204
00:12:19,271 --> 00:12:22,071
Not bad. Get it.

205
00:12:23,404 --> 00:12:26,804
How can I go do volunteer work
in something like this?

206
00:12:26,804 --> 00:12:29,537
Not bad. Get it.

207
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:33,404
This is more fit for a resort.

208
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:36,237
Not bad. Get it.

209
00:12:38,204 --> 00:12:40,503
That's bad. Get it.

210
00:12:52,570 --> 00:12:54,338
Not bad.

211
00:12:54,338 --> 00:12:56,237
Wear it home.

212
00:13:04,670 --> 00:13:06,870
The car will be ready in a few days.

213
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:09,004
Seeing that we haven't maxed out
their credit card yet,

214
00:13:09,004 --> 00:13:11,104
Seo Yun Jae's face must be worth quite a bit.

215
00:13:11,104 --> 00:13:14,104
Yun Jae's parents were flustered.

216
00:13:14,104 --> 00:13:17,071
Yun Jae used to be such a sweet son.

217
00:13:17,071 --> 00:13:19,870
A sweet son would only
make things hard for you.

218
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:21,870
They need to know the world

219
00:13:21,870 --> 00:13:24,137
is not full of sweet sons
and that there can be

220
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:25,904
bad sons like me.

221
00:13:33,071 --> 00:13:34,870
What's the matter?

222
00:13:37,404 --> 00:13:40,804
I keep playing along with you,

223
00:13:40,804 --> 00:13:44,237
and that makes me feel bad toward Yun Jae.

224
00:13:46,004 --> 00:13:48,338
If this is too hard for you,

225
00:13:48,338 --> 00:13:51,570
pretend Kang Gyeong Jun is gone.

226
00:13:51,570 --> 00:13:54,338
Seo Yun Jae's back in here.

227
00:13:55,404 --> 00:13:56,970
The switchover makes me sick, so...

228
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:01,770
Ow.

229
00:14:01,770 --> 00:14:04,237
Kang Gyeong Jun's leaving.

230
00:14:04,237 --> 00:14:07,237
He's coming. He's coming.

231
00:14:07,237 --> 00:14:10,171
Seo Yun Jae

232
00:14:10,171 --> 00:14:12,037
is here.

233
00:14:13,937 --> 00:14:17,970
It's been a long time, Da Ran.

234
00:14:18,603 --> 00:14:20,537
What are you doing?

235
00:14:20,537 --> 00:14:23,670
You've become even prettier.

236
00:14:23,670 --> 00:14:26,704
I've liked you because you were so pretty.

237
00:14:27,404 --> 00:14:32,271
Apart from a few fine lines,
you're still your pretty self.

238
00:14:33,271 --> 00:14:34,737
Kang Gyeong Jun,

239
00:14:34,737 --> 00:14:36,304
stop it.

240
00:14:36,304 --> 00:14:38,470
I'm Yun Jae.

241
00:14:38,470 --> 00:14:40,737
Oh, right.

242
00:14:41,970 --> 00:14:45,371
Warm hands are my trademark.

243
00:14:45,371 --> 00:14:47,237
Da Ran,

244
00:14:47,237 --> 00:14:49,404
does this warm you up?

245
00:14:49,404 --> 00:14:51,104
Yun Jae?

246
00:14:51,104 --> 00:14:52,603
Cut it out, and bring me back

247
00:14:52,603 --> 00:14:55,503
to reality with that comedy
punchline you know so well.

248
00:14:55,503 --> 00:14:59,004
Oh...

249
00:14:59,004 --> 00:15:01,171
So that's what you're into.

250
00:15:01,171 --> 00:15:03,870
Good grief.

251
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:07,237
Given how serious and well-mannered
I am, I don't know...

252
00:15:11,071 --> 00:15:12,937
Da Ran,

253
00:15:12,937 --> 00:15:15,171
your taste has changed.

254
00:15:15,171 --> 00:15:18,870
I've gotten childish as I've been
spending a lot of time with a kid.

255
00:15:18,870 --> 00:15:21,837
You're into childish things?

256
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:23,071
Well...

257
00:15:23,071 --> 00:15:25,104
Let me sing you song Teddy Bear and Rabbit

258
00:15:25,104 --> 00:15:28,537
have sung for me more times
than I care to count.

259
00:15:40,304 --> 00:15:41,970
Tuning.

260
00:15:42,304 --> 00:15:44,071
Here we go.

261
00:15:47,904 --> 00:15:51,304
Hey! It's Pororo!

262
00:15:52,104 --> 00:15:55,438
♪ Playing is the best ♪

263
00:15:55,438 --> 00:15:58,603
♪ Come, friends ♪

