Let's just admire the paintings.

532
00:36:15,704 --> 00:36:17,503
You seem nervous.

533
00:36:19,770 --> 00:36:22,503
I'm glad I helped you walk.

534
00:36:25,404 --> 00:36:27,870
The person we're meeting is
someone mom knew well,

535
00:36:27,870 --> 00:36:31,271
so even if he's not my father, he'll
probably be able to tell me who is.

536
00:36:32,004 --> 00:36:34,804
Yeah. I'm sure things will go well.

537
00:36:41,637 --> 00:36:44,338
Look at all those flowers.

538
00:36:44,338 --> 00:36:46,171
I wonder what they do with them afterwards.

539
00:36:46,171 --> 00:36:49,438
They'll throw them out, of course.

540
00:36:50,570 --> 00:36:53,237
They're so pretty. I love sunflowers.

541
00:36:53,237 --> 00:36:56,937
If they're going to throw them out,
I should come get them after the show.

542
00:36:56,937 --> 00:37:00,770
Why? Are you going to make
sunflower oil with them?

543
00:37:06,870 --> 00:37:08,537
Yes, mother.

544
00:37:08,537 --> 00:37:11,937
You're coming with me to the gathering
I told you about, right?

545
00:37:12,438 --> 00:37:14,071
Yes.

546
00:37:14,704 --> 00:37:17,404
I'd like to see you today
to prepare you for it.

547
00:37:17,404 --> 00:37:20,770
Yun Jae and I are out right now.

548
00:37:21,704 --> 00:37:24,837
We're at Professor Park Min Gyu's exhibition.

549
00:37:25,470 --> 00:37:30,237
Yun Jae's meeting Professor Park Min Gyu?

550
00:37:30,237 --> 00:37:33,404
Yes, but I don't think
Professor Park's here yet.

551
00:37:33,404 --> 00:37:34,804
Da Ran,

552
00:37:34,804 --> 00:37:37,570
get out of there right away.

553
00:37:37,570 --> 00:37:38,704
Pardon?

554
00:37:38,704 --> 00:37:42,071
Come with Yun Jae to the hotel this instant.

555
00:37:42,837 --> 00:37:47,071
But we're in the middle of something.

556
00:37:47,071 --> 00:37:49,237
Just do as you're told.

557
00:37:52,570 --> 00:37:53,937
Mom,

558
00:37:53,937 --> 00:37:56,804
we're at an art gallery. We can't talk.

559
00:37:57,937 --> 00:38:01,171
Why can't you just tell her no?

560
00:38:02,637 --> 00:38:04,071
Don't answer.

561
00:38:04,071 --> 00:38:06,937
It's not good manners to answer
the phone at an art gallery.

562
00:38:08,271 --> 00:38:11,137
We'll call her back when we get out.

563
00:38:11,137 --> 00:38:12,637
Let's go.

564
00:38:13,870 --> 00:38:16,603
The person you're trying to reach...

565
00:38:26,171 --> 00:38:28,338
There he is.

566
00:38:36,503 --> 00:38:38,570
He's in the middle of an interview.

567
00:38:38,570 --> 00:38:40,404
Let's wait.

568
00:38:51,104 --> 00:38:53,304
He didn't tell me not to come,

569
00:38:53,304 --> 00:38:54,704
so I can go.

570
00:38:59,603 --> 00:39:02,603
Daddy? What is it?

571
00:39:04,037 --> 00:39:07,071
Gyeong Jun's still in a coma.

572
00:39:07,837 --> 00:39:09,704
What?

573
00:39:10,104 --> 00:39:12,670
Who's looking for Gyeong Jun?

574
00:39:14,338 --> 00:39:16,037
Who?

575
00:39:16,438 --> 00:39:17,637
- Thank you for coming.
- Thank you.

576
00:39:17,637 --> 00:39:18,770
Please show him around.

577
00:39:18,770 --> 00:39:19,937
This way, please.

578
00:39:30,503 --> 00:39:32,737
It's been a long time, Yun Jae.

579
00:39:33,438 --> 00:39:35,837
Congratulations on the exhibition.

580
00:39:37,804 --> 00:39:39,737
This is my wife.

581
00:39:40,271 --> 00:39:41,670
Nice to meet you.

582
00:39:41,670 --> 00:39:43,737
Congratulations on the wedding.

583
00:39:43,737 --> 00:39:44,870
Is it just the two of you?

584
00:39:44,870 --> 00:39:46,137
Yes.

585
00:39:46,137 --> 00:39:48,438
There's something I'd like to ask you.

586
00:39:49,137 --> 00:39:51,704
Do you know Ms. Kang Hui Su?

587
00:39:51,704 --> 00:39:54,937
Of course. She was my student.

588
00:39:54,937 --> 00:39:59,870
Then do you know her son,
Kang Gyeong Jun?

589
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:06,637
I did hear you were in an accident.

590
00:40:06,637 --> 00:40:11,104
Do you not remember seeing me last year?

591
00:40:11,503 --> 00:40:13,371
No, sir.

592
00:40:13,371 --> 00:40:15,470
I have amnesia.

593
00:40:17,004 --> 00:40:22,137
Why are you asking about Hui Su and her son?

594
00:40:23,503 --> 00:40:26,004
There's something I'd like you
to check for me.

595
00:40:29,338 --> 00:40:33,037
Is this your painting?

596
00:40:34,004 --> 00:40:35,438
Yun Jae.

597
00:40:35,904 --> 00:40:37,004
Your mother is here.

598
00:40:37,004 --> 00:40:38,237
Hello, Professor Park.

599
00:40:38,237 --> 00:40:40,137
Long time no see.

600
00:40:40,137 --> 00:40:44,404
My husband told you about
Yun Jae's condition, right?

601
00:40:44,404 --> 00:40:46,237
Yes.

602
00:40:46,237 --> 00:40:49,004
I have something to discuss with him.

603
00:40:49,004 --> 00:40:51,204
I'd like to have a word with you first.

604
00:40:51,204 --> 00:40:52,770
- Excuse us.
- Of course.

605
00:40:52,770 --> 00:40:54,004
Excuse me.

606
00:41:00,438 --> 00:41:05,204
I don't know what Yun Jae
wants to know about Hui Su,

607
00:41:05,204 --> 00:41:08,438
but please let him know
I have nothing to tell him.

608
00:41:10,804 --> 00:41:12,271
What is it?

609
00:41:12,271 --> 00:41:15,171
What did you ask Professor Park?

610
00:41:15,171 --> 00:41:17,637
About this kid named Kang Gyeong Jun.

611
00:41:17,637 --> 00:41:18,570
Why?

612
00:41:18,570 --> 00:41:21,071
He's been in a coma after having
gotten into an accident with me.

613
00:41:21,071 --> 00:41:23,603
I'd like to find his father for him.

614
00:41:24,371 --> 00:41:27,137
I heard he knew Kang Gyeong Jun's mother,

615
00:41:27,137 --> 00:41:29,171
so I wanted to ask him if he knew anything.

616
00:41:30,438 --> 00:41:37,104
If you know Professor Park, do you
and dad know Gyeong Jun's mother?

617
00:41:37,104 --> 00:41:39,404
Her name is Kang Hui Su.

618
00:41:39,404 --> 00:41:42,470
We don't know her.

619
00:41:42,470 --> 00:41:44,837
I've never even heard the name before.

620
00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:50,271
Yun Jae, I don't think

621
00:41:50,271 --> 00:41:54,704
it's a good idea for you to get
involved in that kid's affairs.

622
00:41:55,770 --> 00:41:57,503
Dr. Seo.

623
00:42:06,304 --> 00:42:08,570
I'll figure all this stuff out.

624
00:42:08,570 --> 00:42:09,970
Don't worry about it.

625
00:42:15,937 --> 00:42:18,470
That old professor is not your father.

626
00:42:18,837 --> 00:42:19,770
What?

627
00:42:19,770 --> 00:42:22,470
My dad just called,

628
00:42:22,470 --> 00:42:24,904
and he told me your father's looking for you.

629
00:42:27,404 --> 00:42:30,637
I'm sorry I couldn't make it to the wedding.

630
00:42:31,404 --> 00:42:34,804
We're sorry we were so rushed
with the wedding.

631
00:42:35,271 --> 00:42:40,171
Do you know that it was thanks to me
that you two got married?

632
00:42:40,171 --> 00:42:40,970
Pardon?

633
00:42:40,970 --> 00:42:43,970
Yun Jae must not have told you.

634
00:42:43,970 --> 00:42:48,104
You two got together because
of an accident at a wedding, right?

635
00:42:48,104 --> 00:42:49,171
Yes.

636
00:42:49,171 --> 00:42:53,071
Yun Jae was rushing out to meet me when

637
00:42:53,071 --> 00:42:56,304
he crashed into you
trying to catch the bouquet.

638
00:42:56,304 --> 00:43:00,737
Yun Jae was rushing out to see you?

639
00:43:00,737 --> 00:43:02,271
Yes.

640
00:43:03,137 --> 00:43:07,537
He was very grateful to me
for having gotten you two together.

641
00:43:07,537 --> 00:43:11,271
You two look great together.

642
00:43:11,537 --> 00:43:12,404
Professor.

643
00:43:12,404 --> 00:43:14,603
Okay. I'll be right with you.

644
00:43:14,603 --> 00:43:15,970
Excuse me.

645
00:43:21,004 --> 00:43:24,104
But Se Yeong had said

646
00:43:24,104 --> 00:43:26,770
Yun Jae was rushing out to see her.

647
00:43:34,004 --> 00:43:35,371
Let's go.

648
00:43:35,371 --> 00:43:37,237
We don't have to be here anymore.

649
00:43:37,670 --> 00:43:40,503
He's not Gyeong Jun's father.

650
00:43:40,503 --> 00:43:43,670
Gyeong Jun's real father is looking for him.

651
00:43:43,670 --> 00:43:46,204
They'll get to see each other soon.

652
00:43:46,603 --> 00:43:47,670
Really?

653
00:43:47,670 --> 00:43:49,537
That's great.

654
00:43:50,870 --> 00:43:52,570
What's wrong?

655
00:43:53,904 --> 00:43:56,770
I have to meet someone
and check on something.

656
00:43:56,770 --> 00:43:58,570
I have to run.

657
00:44:03,037 --> 00:44:08,271
Why don't we enjoy the exhibition
and then go out for some dinner?

658
00:44:09,371 --> 00:44:13,770
If my dad were more on the ball,
we could've met him right away.

659
00:44:14,470 --> 00:44:18,271
In any case, dad told him where
the hospital was, so he'll come soon.

660
00:44:20,071 --> 00:44:22,004
Maybe I should've gone with her.

661
00:44:23,004 --> 00:44:25,637
Now you know the old man is not your dad.

662
00:44:25,637 --> 00:44:27,603
I should go home.

663
00:44:27,603 --> 00:44:29,503
I think something's come up with Ms. Gil.

664
00:44:29,503 --> 00:44:31,837
Aren't you going to the hospital?

665
00:44:31,837 --> 00:44:34,970
Is Ms. Gil more important to you
than finding your dad?

666
00:44:34,970 --> 00:44:36,071
Yup.

667
00:44:36,071 --> 00:44:39,171
Ms. Gil is more important to me
than the dad I've never met.

668
00:44:39,171 --> 00:44:41,970
She came with me even though she was hurt.

669
00:44:47,503 --> 00:44:50,737
How much would you like for them?

670
00:45:12,037 --> 00:45:13,937
I need to toss them some place

671
00:45:13,937 --> 00:45:17,071
where Gil Da Ran will notice them.

672
00:45:31,637 --> 00:45:33,603
She's not always the most alert.

673
00:45:35,704 --> 00:45:37,904
This looks too set up.

674
00:45:41,104 --> 00:45:44,137
She's too short to see this high up.

675
00:45:45,071 --> 00:45:46,837
Why didn't I think of this sooner?

676
00:45:50,071 --> 00:45:51,271
This is really bad.

677
00:45:51,271 --> 00:45:52,804
This is way too much.

678
00:45:57,804 --> 00:45:59,338
They threw them out.

679
00:45:59,338 --> 00:46:00,603
You should take them.

680
00:46:09,404 --> 00:46:11,404
This is the best.

681
00:46:15,104 --> 00:46:18,371
The day Yun Jae and I met,

682
00:46:18,371 --> 00:46:22,904
he wasn't rushing out

683
00:46:22,904 --> 00:46:24,937
to see you.

684
00:46:24,937 --> 00:46:27,637
What does that matter at this point?

685
00:46:27,637 --> 00:46:30,071
It does matter a lot to me.

686
00:46:35,970 --> 00:46:38,304
I suppose it could.

687
00:46:39,004 --> 00:46:41,603
I thought Yun Jae seemed distracted
right before the wedding

688
00:46:41,603 --> 00:46:44,404
because of me.

689
00:46:44,804 --> 00:46:48,970
But I think there was something
else he was preoccupied with.

690
00:46:49,338 --> 00:46:51,137
And what was that?

691
00:46:51,704 --> 00:46:54,737
I've decided to stay out of it.

692
00:46:55,404 --> 00:46:58,204
In any case,

693
00:46:58,204 --> 00:47:01,004
I'll concede that

694
00:47:01,470 --> 00:47:05,770
it wasn't me who made

695
00:47:05,770 --> 00:47:07,770
Yun Jae waver.

696
00:47:12,137 --> 00:47:13,937
But then

697
00:47:15,071 --> 00:47:21,371
why did Yun Jae have the key
to your apartment?

698
00:47:28,904 --> 00:47:31,338
He never came by.

699
00:47:33,470 --> 00:47:36,837
I had hoped he would come by,

700
00:47:37,804 --> 00:47:42,338
but he never used that key.

701
00:47:42,904 --> 00:47:44,904
Satisfied?

702
00:47:44,904 --> 00:47:47,037
Are you happy now?

703
00:47:49,137 --> 00:47:52,338
After butting in and causing
all that confusion,

704
00:47:52,338 --> 00:47:53,570
that's what you have to say?

705
00:47:53,570 --> 00:47:55,603
What does it matter?

706
00:47:55,603 --> 00:47:58,338
You and Yun Jae are already married.

707
00:48:00,537 --> 00:48:02,371
I'm busy. I have to go.

708
00:48:26,704 --> 00:48:28,637
I should be held accountable.

709
00:48:59,171 --> 00:49:02,770
I have to take care of you
for the rest of my life.

710
00:49:08,737 --> 00:49:13,237
Could you ask me the question

711
00:49:13,237 --> 00:49:14,970
you had asked earlier?

712
00:49:17,904 --> 00:49:20,104
Do you

713
00:49:21,204 --> 00:49:24,237
love me?

714
00:49:25,870 --> 00:49:27,570
Where are you right now?

715
00:49:28,438 --> 00:49:30,271
I'll answer you

716
00:49:30,271 --> 00:49:31,870
in person.

717
00:50:09,304 --> 00:50:11,104
Where have you been?

718
00:50:11,104 --> 00:50:13,237
Why didn't you answer your phone?

719
00:50:22,837 --> 00:50:26,271
You said you wanted them if they were
throwing them out anyway.

720
00:50:26,271 --> 00:50:30,071
They were throwing them out, so I went
out of my way to get them for you.

721
00:50:42,503 --> 00:50:45,304
What's wrong? Don't you like them?

722
00:50:49,137 --> 00:50:51,104
Is something wrong?

723
00:50:51,104 --> 00:50:53,104
Did someone say something to you?

724
00:50:53,104 --> 00:50:55,271
Gyeong Jun,

725
00:50:56,704 --> 00:50:59,104
it was all a misunderstanding.

726
00:51:00,470 --> 00:51:04,204
Yun Jae

727
00:51:04,204 --> 00:51:07,104
never went to Lee Se Yeong.

728
00:51:10,071 --> 00:51:16,071
He really did fall for me,

729
00:51:16,071 --> 00:51:19,004
and he always liked me.

730
00:51:20,637 --> 00:51:24,371
He never went against his word that

731
00:51:24,371 --> 00:51:27,438
he would take care of me.

732
00:51:32,404 --> 00:51:34,637
That's great.

733
00:51:34,637 --> 00:51:36,837
There's nothing for you to be
nervous about anymore.

734
00:51:36,837 --> 00:51:38,804
Congratulations.

735
00:51:45,037 --> 00:51:47,704
It's a good thing you remained
devoted to Seo Yun Jae.

736
00:51:47,704 --> 00:51:49,770
I'm proud of you, Gil Da Ran.

737
00:51:55,371 --> 00:51:57,271
Are you that happy?

738
00:52:00,670 --> 00:52:04,904
Now you can wait happily in anticipation

739
00:52:04,904 --> 00:52:08,371
until Kang Gyeong Jun
disappears from your life.

740
00:52:08,704 --> 00:52:10,338
I won't get in the way.

741
00:52:57,737 --> 00:52:59,004
Da Ran,

742
00:52:59,737 --> 00:53:01,171
so you can't

743
00:53:01,171 --> 00:53:02,537
come with Yun Jae

744
00:53:02,537 --> 00:53:05,137
this weekend to look for pretty rocks?

745
00:53:05,137 --> 00:53:06,837
I heard you were going somewhere
with your mother-in-law.

746
00:53:06,837 --> 00:53:08,371
Is it somewhere nice?

747
00:53:09,204 --> 00:53:10,737
Yeah.

748
00:53:11,770 --> 00:53:15,404
Then should we just ask
Yun Jae to come with us?

749
00:53:15,404 --> 00:53:18,338
Don't. This isn't a good time.

750
00:53:20,770 --> 00:53:22,770
Are you not feeling well?

751
00:53:23,371 --> 00:53:25,204
Did you have a fight with Yun Jae?

752
00:53:25,204 --> 00:53:26,937
You look upset.

753
00:53:26,937 --> 00:53:28,670
It's nothing like that.

754
00:53:31,937 --> 00:53:33,371
[Incoming Call: Yun Jae's Mother]

755
00:53:34,137 --> 00:53:35,737
It's Yun Jae's mother.

756
00:53:36,503 --> 00:53:38,237
Why aren't you answering?

757
00:53:39,438 --> 00:53:41,338
Are you scared of her?

758
00:53:41,338 --> 00:53:42,770
No.

759
00:53:43,338 --> 00:53:44,970
Yes, mother.

760
00:53:46,704 --> 00:53:48,204
Today?

761
00:53:49,371 --> 00:53:52,404
Is Yun Jae's mother giving her a hard time?

762
00:54:07,503 --> 00:54:10,704
I'm trying to lay down the tracks.

763
00:54:10,704 --> 00:54:12,870
Get out of the way.

764
00:54:13,637 --> 00:54:16,603
Get out of the way?

765
00:54:17,004 --> 00:54:20,603
I'm getting in your way too?

766
00:54:20,603 --> 00:54:23,137
They're just stupid train tracks.

767
00:54:24,404 --> 00:54:28,137
You should go and work where the adults are.

768
00:54:28,137 --> 00:54:31,037
Hey. I should be studying and playing too.

769
00:54:31,037 --> 00:54:32,371
I'm too young to work.

770
00:54:32,371 --> 00:54:35,970
What? How old are you?

771
00:54:35,970 --> 00:54:38,338
I'm definitely older than you.

772
00:54:38,338 --> 00:54:40,503
Mind your manners.

773
00:54:41,104 --> 00:54:42,704
Never mind.

774
00:54:42,704 --> 00:54:48,071
In a little while, your warm-handed
doctor will be back.

775
00:54:48,737 --> 00:54:50,171
I'm leaving.

776
00:54:50,637 --> 00:54:52,503
Yun Jae.

777
00:54:53,037 --> 00:54:55,071
Come back soon, Yun Jae.

778
00:54:55,071 --> 00:54:56,637
Rabbit.

779
00:54:58,438 --> 00:54:59,837
It's a secret.

780
00:55:00,603 --> 00:55:01,870
Shhh.

781
00:55:04,404 --> 00:55:06,870
Are you on your way to see Kang Gyeong Jun?

782
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:08,037
Yes.

783
00:55:08,037 --> 00:55:10,304
Someone's here to see him.

784
00:55:10,737 --> 00:55:13,171
Is it that lady who had come by earlier?

785
00:55:13,171 --> 00:55:16,804
No. It's a gentleman this time.

786
00:55:40,338 --> 00:55:42,104
I'm sorry.

787
00:55:44,171 --> 00:55:47,071
You're also my son, and yet...

788
00:56:28,503 --> 00:56:29,704
Dr. Seo.

789
00:56:29,704 --> 00:56:31,037
Yun Jae,

790
00:56:33,271 --> 00:56:34,770
where are you off to?

791
00:56:35,171 --> 00:56:38,704
Is he here by any chance?

792
00:56:39,171 --> 00:56:41,004
I'm not sure.

793
00:56:44,904 --> 00:56:46,937
Can I see you for a second?

794
00:56:48,503 --> 00:56:50,104
Yun Jae,

795
00:56:50,104 --> 00:56:55,503
I'm asking you as the eldest
son of the Gil family.

796
00:56:56,171 --> 00:57:01,404
Is your mother mean to my sister?

797
00:57:01,404 --> 00:57:03,037
Why do you ask?

798
00:57:03,537 --> 00:57:06,071
I think Da Ran's seeing your mother today,

799
00:57:06,071 --> 00:57:09,904
and she's acting like she's being
dragged to the slaughterhouse.

800
00:57:10,503 --> 00:57:12,438
Mom wants to see her?

801
00:57:12,438 --> 00:57:18,338
Da Ran loves you a lot,
so she'll put up with it,

802
00:57:18,338 --> 00:57:20,438
but please don't intimidate her
and make things tough on her.

803
00:57:20,438 --> 00:57:23,837
What's there for her to be intimidated about?

804
00:57:23,837 --> 00:57:26,371
Plus, I'm not the one harassing her.

805
00:57:29,470 --> 00:57:31,503
I told to her to wait happily
and in anticipation.

806
00:57:31,503 --> 00:57:33,304
Why is she being intimidated like a fool?

807
00:57:36,338 --> 00:57:38,204
Here you go.

808
00:57:38,204 --> 00:57:41,704
You two rushed to get married,
so I didn't get a chance

809
00:57:41,704 --> 00:57:43,537
to give them to you sooner.

810
00:57:44,104 --> 00:57:48,271
I've been collecting them over the years
for my daughter-in-law-to-be.

811
00:57:48,870 --> 00:57:51,438
I may have come off as a little rude

812
00:57:51,438 --> 00:57:54,704
because you didn't meet my expectations.

813
00:57:55,171 --> 00:57:58,904
Let's get past that and work this out.

814
00:57:58,904 --> 00:58:04,870
It's you who Yun Jae chose to spend
the rest of his life with, after all.

815
00:58:07,104 --> 00:58:09,071
I can't

816
00:58:10,171 --> 00:58:13,004
accept these.

817
00:58:13,338 --> 00:58:14,870
What?

818
00:58:14,870 --> 00:58:17,570
I...

819
00:58:17,570 --> 00:58:21,804
I don't deserve these.

820
00:58:21,804 --> 00:58:26,837
Are you doing this to spite me right now?

821
00:58:27,503 --> 00:58:30,004
No.

822
00:58:30,004 --> 00:58:33,137
I know

823
00:58:33,137 --> 00:58:38,404
I fail to you meet your expectations,
but that's not all.

824
00:58:38,404 --> 00:58:41,004
I'm the very worst.

825
00:58:42,037 --> 00:58:44,804
Even when Yun Jae was by my side,

826
00:58:44,804 --> 00:58:49,104
I was always unsure of myself and nervous.

827
00:58:49,904 --> 00:58:58,204
That's why I didn't trust him
and tried to forget him.

828
00:58:59,304 --> 00:59:04,438
I'm a really bad person.

829
00:59:04,837 --> 00:59:09,537
If you know you're not good enough
for him, it's not too late to let him go.

830
00:59:11,137 --> 00:59:14,137
Yun Jae's not his normal self right now,

831
00:59:14,137 --> 00:59:17,570
which is why I let him do as he pleased.

832
00:59:18,271 --> 00:59:22,338
I couldn't care less if
you were to leave him.

833
00:59:36,271 --> 00:59:38,137
Not now though.

834
00:59:38,137 --> 00:59:39,937
He needs me

835
00:59:40,603 --> 00:59:42,704
right now.

836
00:59:42,704 --> 00:59:45,071
Then

837
00:59:45,071 --> 00:59:47,637
if Yun Jae returns to his normal self

838
00:59:47,637 --> 00:59:52,104
and doesn't need you anymore,
can you let him go then?

839
00:59:55,438 --> 00:59:56,603
Yes.

840
00:59:56,603 --> 01:00:00,503
If you know you don't deserve
to be with Yun Jae,

841
01:00:00,503 --> 01:00:02,904
are you ready to let him go?

842
01:00:03,637 --> 01:00:07,904
If Yun Jae returns to his old self,

843
01:00:08,637 --> 01:00:12,438
I will tell him how bad I've been

844
01:00:13,537 --> 01:00:15,970
and let him go.

845
01:00:47,704 --> 01:00:49,670
Have you been crying?

846
01:00:49,670 --> 01:00:51,837
Don't worry about it.

847
01:00:52,737 --> 01:00:54,137
Let's go.

848
01:00:54,137 --> 01:00:55,137
Go where?

849
01:00:55,137 --> 01:00:56,404
She made you cry.

850
01:00:56,404 --> 01:00:58,737
I'm going to make her pay for making you cry.

851
01:00:58,737 --> 01:01:01,371
I'll make sure I get you what
Yun Jae's face is worth.

852
01:01:01,371 --> 01:01:02,937
Stop it.

853
01:01:04,037 --> 01:01:05,537
Why?

854
01:01:05,537 --> 01:01:08,271
Yun Jae won't be able to defend you,
so I'll do it in his place.

855
01:01:12,770 --> 01:01:16,837
I'll have to hold off on
returning to the States.

856
01:01:17,804 --> 01:01:20,537
I'm way too worried about Yun Jae.

857
01:01:20,937 --> 01:01:23,204
I met Gyeong Jun.

858
01:01:26,004 --> 01:01:30,171
You and Yun Jae

859
01:01:30,171 --> 01:01:32,171
need to meet him too.

860
01:01:33,937 --> 01:01:35,870
If you're not up to it,

861
01:01:36,503 --> 01:01:39,570
I'll have Yun Jae meet him at least.

862
01:01:41,637 --> 01:01:43,137
Let go.

863
01:01:43,670 --> 01:01:45,037
Let go of me.

864
01:01:45,037 --> 01:01:46,770
Stop it.

865
01:01:47,204 --> 01:01:48,870
Don't. I can't do it.

866
01:01:48,870 --> 01:01:50,438
Why not?

867
01:01:50,438 --> 01:01:52,670
I told you to wait happily in anticipation.

868
01:01:52,670 --> 01:01:54,670
Why do you keep getting hurt
and crying over it?

869
01:01:54,670 --> 01:01:56,171
You're making it hard for me
to see you like this!

870
01:01:56,171 --> 01:01:58,603
If it's hard for you to see me like this,
then look away!

871
01:01:58,603 --> 01:02:00,537
I've been doing a good job
being an adult and bearing with it.

872
01:02:00,537 --> 01:02:02,371
Why are you getting in the way?

873
01:02:02,804 --> 01:02:04,171
Taking it all like a fool is being an adult?

874
01:02:04,171 --> 01:02:06,137
Being an adult is bearing with
what you can't change.

875
01:02:06,137 --> 01:02:09,470
Being an adult is about not doing
what you know is bad.

876
01:02:09,470 --> 01:02:12,804
It's only kids that do as they please
even when they know

877
01:02:12,804 --> 01:02:14,503
what they're doing is bad.

878
01:02:16,338 --> 01:02:19,304
So can I do as I please since I'm a kid?

879
01:02:19,304 --> 01:02:21,004
If you cry one more time,

880
01:02:21,004 --> 01:02:22,870
I don't care who you're waiting for.

881
01:02:22,870 --> 01:02:25,204
I'm going to take you far away from here.

882
01:02:53,937 --> 01:02:55,404
[Big]

883
01:02:55,603 --> 01:02:57,204
Don't hold onto to the ring like that.

884
01:02:57,204 --> 01:03:00,204
Do you really think I'll take it
while you're doing the dishes?

885
01:03:00,503 --> 01:03:02,071
Are you suggesting we abandon
Gyeong Jun again?

886
01:03:02,071 --> 01:03:03,737
You must choose.

887
01:03:03,737 --> 01:03:06,137
Will it be Yun Jae and me or Kang Gyeong Jun?

888
01:03:06,137 --> 01:03:08,304
What is it that you're bearing?

889
01:03:08,304 --> 01:03:09,570
Is it Seo Yun Jae who you miss

890
01:03:09,570 --> 01:03:11,704
or is it his mother, the show off?

891
01:03:11,704 --> 01:03:14,071
Gyeong Jun's father was here?

892
01:03:14,071 --> 01:03:15,737
I'm in the hospital lobby

893
01:03:15,737 --> 01:03:17,603
where I've arranged
to meet with your dad.

894
01:03:17,603 --> 01:03:19,104
Are you close by?

895
01:03:22,637 --> 01:03:24,570
She was buying a birthday gift for a guy.

896
01:03:24,570 --> 01:03:28,770
She took off the wedding ring
as she waited for him.

897
01:03:30,237 --> 01:03:32,237
You're done for, Gil Da Ran.
